        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23055",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You should be able to find this \"non\"-bug yourself.\n\nFirst: TMX includes the language within the translation file. It is also possible to have multiple languages within one TMX file.\n\nSecond: Your code differs in one emminent point. You set the locale in your first example on the file \"commons.tmx\", \"another.tmx\" is not available at the time you set your locale. Whereas you set the locale  in your second example on the file \"another.tmx\". So I would expect that \"another.tmx\" includes other languages than \"commons.tmx\".\n\nRelated to your initial problem, I would expect that your browsers are configured differently (one \"en\" and the other \"ru\" for example). When you do not set a locale yourself it will detect the one from the browser. You can read all about this behaviour within the manual. Therefor we have written it. :-)\n\nAnd as you gave no detailed data we can only expect what's going on in your environment and not give detailed help.\n\nSo the conclusio is: This is not a bug and you should always set what you want to be returned.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-07-24T23:42:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-07-24T23:42:37.000+0000"
                }
            ]
